<subSubSection pageId="55" pageNumber="763" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="55.[1990,2583,1154,1573]" pageId="55" pageNumber="763">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1990,2225,1342,1375]" pageId="55" pageNumber="763">Descriptive notes.</emphasis>
Head-body 230-285 mm, tail 210-230 mm; weight c.433 g. The Siberut Flying Squirrel is a large species of Petinomys and uniformly smoky brownish black above and below. Tail is indistinctly distichous. Each cheek has small bump, with 3-4 whiskers.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
